commit.message:
Handle correctly single "%" and "%%" sequences in macro expansion

clsync segfaults on non-terminated % or %% sequences. This patch fixes
this by allocating necessary data.

However macro expansion still doesn't work properly on complex cases
like %%text%% or %txt1%%txt2%: clsync continues to work normally, but
macro is not expanded the way it was supposed to.

commit.message:
Fix parallel build issues in LTO mode

In LTO mode is used -flto=jobserver to facilitate slow LTO process
on SMP systems, but this requires jobserver and unfortunately
automake doesn't generate rules properly, so we need to patch them.

This solution is somewhat ugly, but works fine and the best we can
do.

commit.message:
bugfix: Do not ignore *-{uid,gid} settings if no CAPABILITIES_SUPPORT

Even with configuration:
```
uid = 1000
gid = 1000
privileged-uid = %uid%
privileged-gid = %gid%
sync-handler-uid = %uid%
sync-handler-gid = %gid%
```

clsync was running rsync with setuid(0) on Fedora. Fixing it.

configure.ac: use target instead of host

Use AC_CANONICAL_TARGET instead of +AC_CANONICAL_HOST to check for
target_os instead of host_os: this is correct behaviour during
cross-compilation.

Of course clsync as a whole is not ready for cross-compilation yet.

commit.message:
sync.c: Simplify structure zero initialization

According to the C standard all static objects are guaranteed to be 0,
so even "= {0}" is surplus, though it makes coding intention more understandable.

This gets rid of -Wmissing-field-initializers warning.
